race.comment: The BM56 from Hanging Rock on Australia Day looks the key form reference here. HI TIAGO won it, but it was hard to fault the run of MARTY MCFLY (1), who didn't seem to appreciate racing in behind the leaders and did not get out until too late. Finished off stylishly once into the clear to run HI TIAGO to 1.25 lengths and while given no favours at the barrier draw, the bigger track here might suit. FIGHTTHEGOODFIGHT (9) comes through the same race and wasn't beaten far in fourth spot, but she was only first-up that day so will have improvement to come. EL SALTO (3) ran his worst race in ages last start, so give another chance. TANGEOETTE (11) resumes. Last first up outing returned a maiden win and can fire fresh again off two trials.
